CatDescriptText: Edward B. Smith, county employee, 704 Junilla Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Do you think the Little Rock, Ark. school integration incident will gain more financial support for the NAACP in its continuing fight for equal rights?"  Answer reads: "I think it will gain more financial support for the NAACP in its continued fight for equal rights."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Edward B. Smith standing with left hand on trunk of Ford car with Fordomatic Drive, parked on unknown street with storefronts in background
